<topic id="dcpp_how_to_flag_content_using_change_bars">
  <title>How to Flag Content Using Change Bars </title>
  <body>
    <p>As an example, to add a <term>change bar</term> (revision mark) for particular content, you
      can use the following in the DITAVAL
      file:<codeblock outputclass="language-xml">&lt;val>
  &lt;revprop action="flag" 
    changebar="color:blue;style:solid;width:2pt;offset:1.25mm;placement:start" val="new"/>
&lt;/val></codeblock></p>
    <p>This would result in any content that is marked with <xmlatt>rev="new"</xmlatt> having a blue
      change bar.</p>
  </body>
</topic>
